Interface PageElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable, Trashable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ContentElement
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractContentElement, Box, Page, ProxyServer

    public interface PageElement
extends Trashable, Serializable
    Represents an element in a page.

    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

    • Method Detail

      • getChildPageElements

        List<? extends PageElement> getChildPageElements(CmsRequest<?> context)
        Get the children of this page element based on the passed context. The returned list of child elements is context specific and may not represent all possible page elements that can be returned.

        CMS will process and render this list automatically if the generator returned by this PageElement calls ProcessChain.processChildElements() and RenderChain.renderChildElements().

        Parameters:
        context - the context
        Returns:
        a list of child elements.

      • getComponentIdentifier

        String getComponentIdentifier()
        Get the component identifier. For backward compatibility, base components are not required to have a component identifier.
        Returns:
        the component identifier. May be null.

        Returns:

      • getGenerator

        @Nullable
Generator<? extends PageElement> getGenerator(CmsRequest<? extends PageElement> request)
        Get a generator instance for the specified content type. This method will be called once per request by CMS internals. This is not intended to be used by ContentElement/Generator implementors.
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the generator. Return null to indicate that a generator isn't supported for the specified request.
